cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the problem of finding the largest empty axis-parallel box amidst a point configuration. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the volume of the largest empty box, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper involves proving a lower bound on the volume of the largest empty box, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
